==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plancher
<hw>Planch"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
<ets>planche</ets>. See <er>Planch</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A floor
of wood; also, a plank.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The under side of a cornice; a
soffit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plancher</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plancher
<hw>Planch"er</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To form of planks.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Golding.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Planchet</ent>⟦br⟧
